paragraphs.title: Register auth events as table so we can query
Which users log into many distinct hosts?
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql

select user, count(distinct(ip_dst_host)) as distinct_systems from auth_events where auth_orientation = 'LogOn' group by user order by distinct_systems desc limit 100

paragraphs.title: Distinct host logons by time
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql
select 
    from_unixtime(timestamp/1000,'YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm') as time,
   count( distinct(ip_dst_host)) as distinct_systems
from auth_events
where user = "${user}" and auth_orientation = 'LogOn'
group by from_unixtime(timestamp/1000,'YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm')

paragraphs.title: Number of Logons by Time
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql
select 
    from_unixtime(timestamp/1000,'YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm') as time,
   count(*) as num_logons
from auth_events
where user = "${user}" and auth_orientation = 'LogOn'
group by from_unixtime(timestamp/1000,'YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm')

paragraphs.title: List of Hosts Accessed by User
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql
select ip_dst_host, count(*) as num_logons from auth_events where  user = "${user}" and auth_orientation = 'LogOn' group by ip_dst_host order by num_logons desc
